revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-06-01 16:23:08.000000000', 'files': ['nailgun/nailgun/utils/logs.py'], 'message': "fix race with syslog while renaming remote log dir

When a node gets new name nailgun renmaes log directoty
which had name in for mof <IP> to <node name> and then
creates symlink <IP> -> <node name>. The problem is that
node is still active and this moment and sends some logs
to syslog on master node.

So when we renamed <IP> to <node name> and haven't created
symlink name syslog may find missing log dir and it creates
it again in this case. Then nailgun tries to create symlink
and fails.

To avoid this situation we can suspend rsyslog temporarity.
It's better to do it with SIGSTOP/SIGCONT, because process
exist in this case and remote logs will be held in kernel
tcp or odp buffers until we wake up rsyslog and it process
new messages. Fortunately centos-7 uses journald together
with rsyslog, so local logs (send by syslog function) are
handled by journald and rsyslog just get it from journald
files. So it's safe to stop rsyslog temporarily, nothing
will be droppped.

Change-Id: Icb1ed6669be2f7b448c465de33de37e0b945fb79
Closes-Bug: #1506112
(cherry picked from commit 6e49910fcadf52cdeff235b0795f0dde2f63f60a)
"}]
commit_message:
fix race with syslog while renaming remote log dir

When a node gets new name nailgun renmaes log directoty
which had name in for mof <IP> to <node name> and then
creates symlink <IP> -> <node name>. The problem is that
node is still active and this moment and sends some logs
to syslog on master node.

So when we renamed <IP> to <node name> and haven't created
symlink name syslog may find missing log dir and it creates
it again in this case. Then nailgun tries to create symlink
and fails.

To avoid this situation we can suspend rsyslog temporarity.
It's better to do it with SIGSTOP/SIGCONT, because process
exist in this case and remote logs will be held in kernel
tcp or odp buffers until we wake up rsyslog and it process
new messages. Fortunately centos-7 uses journald together
with rsyslog, so local logs (send by syslog function) are
handled by journald and rsyslog just get it from journald
files. So it's safe to stop rsyslog temporarily, nothing
will be droppped.

Change-Id: Icb1ed6669be2f7b448c465de33de37e0b945fb79
Closes-Bug: #1506112
(cherry picked from commit 6e49910fcadf52cdeff235b0795f0dde2f63f60a)

commit_message:
Adding new repository trove-image-builder

The trove-image-builder project will contain tools to help users build
guest images for use with OpenStack Trove.

The trove-image-builder project will share Gerrit permissions with
trove and therefore a new ACL file has not been created. The
documentation has been updated to reflect Craig's comment; that review
is https://review.openstack.org/#/c/312893/

It will be initially populated with existing elements from the
trove-integration project.

Change-Id: I65d5da58594854b155dc6ba7f3ceabaea6f61cc5
Needed-By: Ic60872d1cd20120357907722b27530cc6d78b6e5
Related: I823d5d611cf951360e11c4564c7e4696a586916d

deliverable files where the page doesn't exist yet.

commit_message:
Add lxc1 as a dependency for all Ubuntu hosts

The new Rackspace Ubuntu 16.04 Xenial public cloud image does
not include the 'lxc1' package by default, which provides lxc
userspace tools.  But independent of whether this is correct
or not, we should ensure that lxc1 is installed always.

Change-Id: I1022cfa2dad365db64ce61fa7db9aed744c36eb3
Signed-off-by: Michael Davies <michael@the-davies.net>

revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2016-05-27 13:57:58.000000000', 'files': ['specs/newton/approved/pagination-and-changes-since-for-instance-action-list.rst'], 'message': 'Add pagination and changes since filter support for os-isntance-action API

Currently, os-instance-actions  API does not support pagination.
As in production deployment the number of instance action records
can be also very large query them all can lead to performance
bottleneck, it will be very useful to support pagination.

Also, os-instance-actions API does not support filter the migration
record by last updated time. As for production deployment, an instance
can be up for a very long time, and the number of migration records
will also be very big. It will be very useful to support filter by
last update time.

APIImpact
DocImpact

Change-Id: I9ac4d73c120292fbe9e075d5da2549bdf6a6feaf
Implements: blueprint pagination-add-changes-since-for-instance-action-list
'}]
commit_message:
Add pagination and changes since filter support for os-isntance-action API

Currently, os-instance-actions  API does not support pagination.
As in production deployment the number of instance action records
can be also very large query them all can lead to performance
bottleneck, it will be very useful to support pagination.

Also, os-instance-actions API does not support filter the migration
record by last updated time. As for production deployment, an instance
can be up for a very long time, and the number of migration records
will also be very big. It will be very useful to support filter by
last update time.

APIImpact
DocImpact

Change-Id: I9ac4d73c120292fbe9e075d5da2549bdf6a6feaf
Implements: blueprint pagination-add-changes-since-for-instance-action-list
